Usage: pyloc.py directory [-v]

Where directory is the directory to scan and -v will cause verbose output.

Example basic output:
---------------------

[james@collingwood pyloc]$ ./pyloc.py /home/james/projects-git/haskellhead/ 

    PYLOC
    -----
    Folder   : /home/james/projects-git/haskellhead/

    Summary
    -------
    Haskell: 99.04%
    Shell: 0.96%

    TOTAL physical SLOC : 1,775

Example verbose output:
-----------------------

[james@collingwood pyloc]$ ./pyloc.py /home/james/projects-svn/mosaic/src/ -v

    PYLOC
    -----
    Folder   : /home/james/projects-svn/mosaic/src/

    XML (300 files) :
            Code       : 71,584
            Comments   : 1,448
            Whitespace : 1,775

            Physical SLOC : 74,807

    JSP (1,040 files) :
